t major dungeons, though it does vary a little, even night to night.<br><br>Most people, including those in 'FFA' guilds, do respect reasonably held xp camps of others, not because they have to, but just because its the decent thing to do, and they don't want the 'arrogant asshole' reputation. Reasonableness, communication, cooperation, these words have meaning.<br><br>Those few who do not so respect reasonably held camps better have a good group of like-minded friends, or they will wonder why they are LFG / can't get a port / can't get a rez so much. Perhaps due to how they make other people around them feel?<br><br>Think about where you want to be, Binkee. I've nothing against you personally, I do not know you, but I'd think twice about inviting anyone with an antagonistic 'stuff anyone else, I will take what I want no matter how much it upsets you' viewpoint into my groups, and I know many others do also. I see some folks who use statements like yours here LFG in Seb so often, and I bet some of them have no clue why.<br><br>Just think about it, ok?<br> <p>------------------------------------------------<BR><BR><TABLE width = 80% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><TR align="left"><H6><TH><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=49771">Venerable Felishanna Secretlight</A><BR></TH><TH>Felishanna</TH></H6></TR><TR><FONT size=4><TD HEIGHT=16>High Priestess of Tunare</TD><TD>Cleric of Tunare of 21 Seasons</TD></TR><TR><TD HEIGHT=16>Guild: <A HREF="http://pub36.ezboard.com/bheroes795">Heroes of the Old Lands</A></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD HEIGHT=16>Server: <A HREF="http://server6.ezboard.com/beqasylum">Lanys T'Vyl</A></TD><TD>Server: <A HREF="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie">Firiona Vie</A></TD></TR><TR><TD HEIGHT=16><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Id=49771">[Journal]</A>  <A HREF="http://eq.castersr